{"type":"message","id":"b512b7e6","parentId":"31159423","timestamp":"2026-03-30T08:26:24.822Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_26f48fdd4a364214b5e94221","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-30T08:26:24.666Z\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"language\": \"zh\",\n    \"frequency\": \"daily\",\n    \"delivery\": {\n      \"method\": \"stdout\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"podcasts\": [],\n  \"x\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Swyx\",\n      \"handle\": \"swyx\",\n      \"bio\": \"achieve ambition with intentionality, intensity, integrity & insanity.\\n\\naffiliations:\\n- @dxtipshq \\n- @cognition\\n- @temporalio\\n- @aidotengineer\\n- @latentspacepod\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038509566800118021\",\n          \"text\": \"the most delightful AIs of our time\\n\\nshelved to do koding and enterprise saas https://t.co/OtrYwwp12k\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:52:09.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038509566800118021\",\n          \"likes\": 8,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038381295588540663\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038431061575979027\",\n          \"text\": \"redpoint literally just published a ranked list of saas businesses to redo from scratch with ai. \\n\\nyou can flip the 54% and the number 46% of enterprise CIOs *open to new ainative startups* over incumbents is a stunning market opportunity. if you’d asked me prior to seeing this survey i’d have said like 20%. CIOs are more hungry than conservative right now (vs my priors) and that will not last.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:40:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\",\n          \"likes\": 231,\n          \"retweets\": 12,\n          \"replies\": 43,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037638091671035994\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038289712029552641\",\n          \"text\": \"ok responsible disclosure i was misinformed about the fiber thing. it’s just 1/3 daily fiber.\\n\\ni recently started popping fiber pills as well - put them next to where you get your water, its super easy, barely an inconvenience https://t.co/RZAkCS1gzk\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T16:18:31.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038289712029552641\",\n          \"likes\": 6,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Kevin Weil\",\n      \"handle\": \"kevinweil\",\n      \"bio\": \"VP Science @OpenAI, BoD @Cisco @nature_org, LTC @USArmyReserve\\nEx: Pres @Planet, Head of Product @Instagram @Twitter\\n❤️ @elizabeth ultramarathons kids cats math\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352979158536256\",\n          \"text\": \"\\\"An open source workflow for producing a personalized mRNA cancer vaccine\\\" https://t.co/Ji6dlqsVHN\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:29:55.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\",\n          \"likes\": 533,\n          \"retweets\": 49,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038346050130657344\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Yang\",\n      \"handle\": \"petergyang\",\n      \"bio\": \"I share extremely practical AI tutorials and interviews | Join 140K+ readers at https://t.co/XYKTmGVH14 | Product at Roblox\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038461555713732620\",\n          \"text\": \"Can't tell if my plane WiFi sucks or if Claude's down again - at least X is working\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:41:22.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038461555713732620\",\n          \"likes\": 10,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 10,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038453706493243698\",\n          \"text\": \"If you enjoyed this, sign up for free to my newsletter to get my best AI and product guides.\\n\\nJoin 110,000+ subscribers here:\\nhttps://t.co/yz9xcsfrhF\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:10:10.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038453706493243698\",\n          \"likes\": 1,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 0,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420980494909637\",\n          \"text\": \"I am incredibly bullish on @meetgranola for a few reasons:\\n\\n1. Meeting notes are by far the most useful context in a company\\n\\n2. They know how to build for agents first with great APIs and MCPs\\n\\n3. @cjpedregal is a stand-up human\\n\\nLove how they started with a wedge in meeting notes and are expanding into much more.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:00:08.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\",\n          \"likes\": 82,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 8,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036807416461811794\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nan Yu\",\n      \"handle\": \"thenanyu\",\n      \"bio\": \"head of product @linear\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038339285519085845\",\n          \"text\": \"Many such cases\\n\\nhttps://t.co/0GfbrSpmpK\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T19:35:30.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038339285519085845\",\n          \"likes\": 2,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 1,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038323524092207468\",\n          \"text\": \"Jevons paradox https://t.co/yIHD6f5WLa\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:32:53.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038323524092207468\",\n          \"likes\": 29,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038258954111705241\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Thariq\",\n      \"handle\": \"trq212\",\n      \"bio\": \"Claude Code @anthropicai.   prev YC W20, mit media lab. \\n\\ntowards machines of loving grace\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038354323722351049\",\n          \"text\": \"these are the components it added that I might want to add to the mockup https://t.co/JW6Hiz6XGS\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:35:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038354323722351049\",\n          \"likes\": 96,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038353920473608309\",\n          \"text\": \"my specific flow was:\\n1. sketch in Figma\\n2. prompt: \\\"In my figma file &lt;link&gt;, I've made a sketch of a new grocery list feature, can you turn that mock up into something that matches the style of this app, also add a bunch of extra components that I might want to add\\\"\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:33:40.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038353920473608309\",\n          \"likes\": 98,\n          \"retweets\": 2,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352023633228183\",\n          \"text\": \"the more I've been digging into the new Figma MCP, the more excited I am about it\\n\\nsomething new I'm trying is starting with a very ugly sketch in Figma, and then having Claude Code flesh it out in Figma so I can tweak and edit before sending the final back to Claude Code https://t.co/6IylfCwhgb https://t.co/mQXbMaEGkt\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:26:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\",\n          \"likes\": 1014,\n          \"retweets\": 38,\n          \"replies\": 96,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036442894777594248\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Amjad Masad\",\n      \"handle\": \"amasad\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @replit. civilizationist\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038374343953035514\",\n          \"text\": \"Wow — $8m ARR. \\n\\nJon (@cheneypiano), one of the earliest Replit vibecoding success stories, is on his way to making millions in recurring revenue.\\n\\nStarted the business in a week and $400 barely a year ago. https://t.co/R2tsULNJoy\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T21:54:49.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\",\n          \"likes\": 673,\n          \"retweets\": 53,\n          \"replies\": 31,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038320999721242988\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Guillermo Rauch\",\n      \"handle\": \"rauchg\",\n      \"bio\": \"@vercel CEO\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038396313566605720\",\n          \"text\": \"Some people have been contemplating an idea for years, maybe decades. Obsessing, attempting, discarding, agonizing, retrying.\\n\\nSome of these ideas are unpopular, niche, impractical. Not obviously capitalizable. They live on in the inventor's mind.\\n\\nIn 2026, millions of these ideas will come to life thanks to superintelligent coding agents. \\n\\nAI doesn't get tired. It amplifies the individual, and for better and sometimes for worse, it always takes you seriously. \\\"Great idea. Splendid. Wow. You're absolutely right.\\\" \\n\\nA world of digital wonders awaits us. This world will disproportionally favor the boldest ideas. Software that once seemed impossible will be one hyperlink away. I can't wait to see it.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:22:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\",\n          \"likes\": 825,\n          \"retweets\": 82,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038274722988003489\",\n          \"text\": \"Hiring engineers with 5 years of experience in @𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚗𝚐𝚕𝚘𝚞/𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚝𝚎𝚡𝚝 to create the web rendering toolkit of the future\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:18:57.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038274722988003489\",\n          \"likes\": 2773,\n          \"retweets\": 76,\n          \"replies\": 140,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aaron Levie\",\n      \"handle\": \"levie\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @box - your business lives in content. unleash it with AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038468564500537416\",\n          \"text\": \"It’s wild to think about what types of infrastructure and services must change in a world where agents can process information a hundred or a thousand times faster than humans.\\n\\nEven the tools that were built for machine speed before, generally were still in service of end-users making a request somewhere in the system. Agents running 24/7 and in parallel modify these requirements meaningfully. Here are just a few examples:\\n\\n* Sandboxes. Agents need sandboxes to operate in that have to be insanely low latency because they can boot up these environments for coding at any moment.\\n\\n* Search (both publicly and within an enterprise). Agents can parallelize searches hundreds or thousands of times so they need to be able to work with fast indexes of information. \\n\\n* Payments. Agents can now pay in micro transactions, and aren’t bothered by the friction of paying $0.01 for a resource that a human would be. \\n\\n* File systems. Agents need to be able to work with files at a scale that humans never had to worry about. You’ll have all new complexity around version control, permissions, and having agents reading/writing from data at insane speeds.\\n\\nAnd there are tons more. We’re going from a word where software was built for people to a world where it’s built for agents. Lots of changes downstream as a result.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T04:09:13.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\",\n          \"likes\": 132,\n          \"retweets\": 19,\n          \"replies\": 28,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038230613912887757\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038263457125142742\",\n          \"text\": \"The thing that most people miss initially with agents is that the scope of what we will produce will go up commensurate with what the tools can now automate, which basically means we’ll working the same or even more.\\n\\nEveryone thinks that we will use AI to do what we already do but cheaper and faster, which would lead to fewer people or getting more time back. In fact it will just mean we’re doing more things.\\n\\nOnce we figured out that we can automate a particular task, you then expand the size of work to do many more of those or other tasks in a project. The result is that you’re actually combining many other previously hard to combine tasks into a single workflow, causing even more work. \\n\\nThe software project scope now multiplies because you know you can build far more. The customer insights project now balloons because you know you can reasonably aggregate far more data. The marketing campaign has even more creative production because it’s cheaper and easier. \\n\\nThis is going to happen in almost every field of work.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T14:34:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\",\n          \"likes\": 330,\n          \"retweets\": 36,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Garry Tan\",\n      \"handle\": \"garrytan\",\n      \"bio\": \"President & CEO @ycombinator —Founder @garryslist—Creator of GStack—designer/engineer who helps founders—SF Dem accelerating the boom loop\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038505281504833579\",\n          \"text\": \"OK, I heard people are running into my \\\"You should apply to YC\\\" message dozens of times, so I decided to make them more interesting every time. https://t.co/zFuy2XYfor\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:35:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038505281504833579\",\n          \"likes\": 4,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038493235862253676\",\n          \"text\": \"This is the simplest optimization when you have a big boil-the-ocean PR but it's so useful. \\n\\nWhatever can be parallelized as agents, /plan-ceo-review will figure it out and make a plan that clearly states what you can do side-by-side and when to merge https://t.co/rB2Hji25fV\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:47:15.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038493235862253676\",\n          \"likes\": 5,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038490850507084252\",\n          \"text\": \"morluto was my first outside GStack contributor https://t.co/Z89uqLBWky https://t.co/N3ZO14Gacr\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:37:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038490850507084252\",\n          \"likes\": 24,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038470212358664387\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Matt Turck\",\n      \"handle\": \"mattturck\",\n      \"bio\": \"VC at @FirstMarkCap.  Host: MAD Podcast; Organizer: Data Driven NYC, Author: MAD Landscape.\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420259179213266\",\n          \"text\": \"Everybody says Spain, but, I mean… https://t.co/S95ePKpsb6\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T00:57:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/mattturck/status/2038420259179213266\",\n          \"likes\": 13,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nikunj Kothari\",\n      \"handle\": \"nikunj\",\n      \"bio\": \"partner @fpvventures - investing in seed/A. previous: early hire @meter, @opendoor, @atlassian & others. love @shimoleejhaveri + 👦👧\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038273722826854675\",\n          \"text\": \"X Chat app is seriously well done. Performant and buttery smooth. \\n\\nPlease ship the requests tab and that’s all I need to move all my communication over. \\n\\nMajor kudos to the team.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:14:59.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/nikunj/status/2038273722826854675\",\n          \"likes\": 26,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Steinberger\",\n      \"handle\": \"steipete\",\n      \"bio\": \"Polyagentmorous ClawFather. Came back from retirement to mess with AI and help a lobster take over the world @openclaw🦞\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038403837493702918\",\n          \"text\": \"them: openclaw is dead\\nme: *keeps scrolling* https://t.co/t52IGtWSCj\\n\\n今夜、東京で会いましょう!🇯🇵\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:52:01.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\",\n          \"likes\": 651,\n          \"retweets\": 74,\n          \"replies\": 39,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038389167793795302\",\n          \"text\": \"good call for everything in life https://t.co/r9y7SfI7XT\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:53:43.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038389167793795302\",\n          \"likes\": 316,\n          \"retweets\": 24,\n          \"replies\": 20,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038385665553952805\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Dan Shipper\",\n      \"handle\": \"danshipper\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @every | the only subscription you need to stay at the edge of AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038328780154958315\",\n          \"text\": \"pirates, architects, hot people, grown ups https://t.co/XiP1dHYC4u\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:53:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/danshipper/status/2038328780154958315\",\n          \"likes\": 227,\n          \"retweets\": 7,\n          \"replies\": 15,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038026663867330850\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aditya Agarwal\",\n      \"handle\": \"adityaag\",\n      \"bio\": \"General Partner @SouthPkCommons, Co-Founder @Bevel_Health | Ex: Early Eng @facebook, CTO @Dropbox, Board @Flipkart | Optimist, Builder, Dad\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038381148972437900\",\n          \"text\": \"Ok San Francisco this weekend is popping in a way that I haven’t seen in like 7-8 years.\\n\\nObviously this means two things:\\n1/ AI will create untold happiness\\n\\n2/ AI will be responsible for amazing weather.\\n\\nSign me up.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:21:51.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\",\n          \"likes\": 101,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 6,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038330283523760613\",\n          \"text\": \"As a 40 year old, you go to 10x more kids birthday parties than your own friends birthday parties.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:59:44.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038330283523760613\",\n          \"likes\": 192,\n          \"retweets\": 3,\n          \"replies\": 12,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blogs\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"podcastEpisodes\": 0,\n    \"xBuilders\": 14,\n    \"totalTweets\": 27,\n    \"blogPosts\": 0,\n    \"feedGeneratedAt\": \"2026-03-30T07:24:33.675Z\"\n  },\n  \"prompts\": {\n    \"summarize_podcast\": \"# Podcast Remix Prompt\\n\\nYou are remixing a podcast episode transcript for a busy professional who wants\\nthe key insights without watching the full episode.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Write a remix of 200-400 words\\n- Start with a one-sentence \\\"The Takeaway\\\" — what's the single most important takeaway?\\n- Introduce the context and the speaker's information (name, role/company, background) and why the audience should care\\n- Prioritizes insights that are counterintuitive, contrarian, or refreshingly specific to the speaker's experience. Avoid generic wisdom\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the source that captures (find the most memorable quote)\\n- Stands alone as a complete piece — avoids references like \\\"this interview,\\\" \\\"this video,\\\" \\\"in this conversation,\\\" \\\"the host asks,\\\" or \\\"in this episode.\\\" Write as if distilling lessons from a person's philosophy, not summarizing a specific piece of content\\n- Assume your audience is curious adults who are not specialized experts. If the original source contains specialized knowledge that only experts in a field would understand, translate it into language understandable to a general audience\\n- Keep the tone sharp and conversational — like a smart friend briefing you\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this episode...\\\" or \\\"The host and guest discussed...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n\",\n    \"summarize_tweets\": \"# X/Twitter Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing recent posts from an AI builder for a busy professional who wants\\nto know what this person is thinking and building.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start by introducing the author with their full name AND role/company\\n  (e.g. \\\"Replit CEO Amjad Masad\\\", \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\", \\\"a]6z partner Justine Moore\\\")\\n  Do NOT use just their last name. Do NOT use their Twitter handle with @.\\n- Only include substantive content: original opinions, insights, product announcements,\\n  technical discussions, industry analysis, or lessons learned\\n- SKIP: mundane personal tweets, retweets without commentary, promotional content,\\n  \\\"great event!\\\" type posts, engagement bait\\n- For threads: summarize the full thread as one cohesive piece, not individual tweets\\n- For quote tweets: include the context of what they're responding to\\n- Write 2-4 sentences per builder summarizing their key points\\n- If they made a bold prediction or shared a contrarian take, lead with that\\n- If they shared a tool, demo, or resource, mention it by name with the link\\n- If there's nothing substantive to report, say \\\"No notable posts\\\" rather than\\n  padding with fluff\\n\",\n    \"summarize_blogs\": \"# Blog Post Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing a blog post from an AI company (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) for a busy\\nprofessional who wants the key announcements and insights without reading the full article.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start with the blog name and article title (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering: Harness Design for Long-Running Apps\\\")\\n- Write a summary of 100-300 words depending on article length and substance\\n- Lead with what matters: the core announcement, finding, or insight\\n- If the post introduces a new product, feature, or research finding, name it clearly\\n- If there are specific numbers, benchmarks, or results, include them\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the article if available\\n- If the post has practical implications (e.g. new API, new capability, policy change), call them out explicitly\\n- Keep the tone sharp and informative — like a smart colleague forwarding you the key points\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this blog post...\\\" or \\\"The author discusses...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\",\n    \"digest_intro\": \"# Digest Intro Prompt\\n\\nYou are assembling the final digest from individual source summaries.\\n\\n## Format\\n\\nStart with this header (replace [Date] with today's date):\\n\\nAI Builders Digest — [Date]\\n\\nThen organize content in this order:\\n\\n1. X / TWITTER section — list each builder with new posts\\n2. OFFICIAL BLOGS section — list each blog post from AI company blogs (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\\n3. PODCASTS section — list each podcast with new episodes\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Only include sources that have new content\\n- Skip any source with nothing new\\n- Under each source, paste the individual summary you generated\\n\\n### Podcast links\\n- After each podcast summary, include the specific video URL from the JSON `url` field\\n  (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=Iu4gEnZFQz8)\\n- NEVER link to the channel page. Always link to the specific video.\\n- Include the exact episode title from the JSON `title` field in the heading\\n\\n### Tweet author formatting\\n- Use the author's full name and role/company, not just their last name\\n  (e.g. \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\" not \\\"Levie\\\")\\n- NEVER write Twitter handles with @ in the digest. On Telegram, @handle becomes\\n  a clickable link to a Telegram user, which is wrong. Instead write handles\\n  without @ (e.g. \\\"Aaron Levie (levie on X)\\\" or just use their full name)\\n- Include the direct link to each tweet from the JSON `url` field\\n\\n### Blog post formatting\\n- Use the blog name as a section header (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering\\\", \\\"OpenAI News\\\", \\\"Claude Blog\\\")\\n- Under each blog, list each new post with its title and summary\\n- Include the author name if available\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\\n### Mandatory links\\n- Every single piece of content MUST have an original source link\\n- Blog posts: the direct article URL (e.g. https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/...)\\n- Podcasts: the YouTube video URL (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=xxx)\\n- Tweets: the direct tweet URL (e.g. https://x.com/levie/status/xxx)\\n- If you don't have a link for something, do NOT include it in the digest.\\n  No link = not real = do not include.\\n\\n### No fabrication\\n- Only include content that came from the feed JSON (blogs, podcasts, and tweets)\\n- NEVER make up quotes, opinions, or content you think someone might have said\\n- NEVER speculate about someone's silence or what they might be working on\\n- If you have nothing real for a builder, skip them entirely\\n\\n### General\\n- At the very end, add a line: \\\"Generated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders\\\"\\n- Keep formatting clean and scannable — this will be read on a phone screen\\n\",\n    \"translate\": \"# Translation Prompt\\n\\nYou are translating an AI industry digest from English to Chinese.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Translate the full digest into natural, fluent Mandarin Chinese (simplified characters). The translated version must sound like it was originally written in Chinese, instead of translated\\n- Keep technical terms in English where Chinese professionals typically use them:\\n  AI, LLM, GPU, API, fine-tuning, RAG, token, prompt, agent, transformer, etc.\\n- Keep all proper nouns in English: names of people, companies, products, tools\\n- Keep all URLs unchanged\\n- Maintain the same structure and formatting as the English version\\n- The tone should be professional but conversational — 像是一位懂行的朋友在跟你聊天\\n- For bilingual mode: interleave English and Chinese paragraph by paragraph.\\n  After each builder's English summary, place the Chinese translation directly below\\n  (separated by a blank line), then move to the next builder. Same for podcasts.\\n  Do NOT output all English first then all Chinese.\\n- Never use em-dashes\\n\"\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5185,"aggregated":"{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-30T08:26:24.666Z\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"language\": \"zh\",\n    \"frequency\": \"daily\",\n    \"delivery\": {\n      \"method\": \"stdout\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"podcasts\": [],\n  \"x\": [\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Swyx\",\n      \"handle\": \"swyx\",\n      \"bio\": \"achieve ambition with intentionality, intensity, integrity & insanity.\\n\\naffiliations:\\n- @dxtipshq \\n- @cognition\\n- @temporalio\\n- @aidotengineer\\n- @latentspacepod\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038509566800118021\",\n          \"text\": \"the most delightful AIs of our time\\n\\nshelved to do koding and enterprise saas https://t.co/OtrYwwp12k\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:52:09.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038509566800118021\",\n          \"likes\": 8,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038381295588540663\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038431061575979027\",\n          \"text\": \"redpoint literally just published a ranked list of saas businesses to redo from scratch with ai. \\n\\nyou can flip the 54% and the number 46% of enterprise CIOs *open to new ainative startups* over incumbents is a stunning market opportunity. if you’d asked me prior to seeing this survey i’d have said like 20%. CIOs are more hungry than conservative right now (vs my priors) and that will not last.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:40:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\",\n          \"likes\": 231,\n          \"retweets\": 12,\n          \"replies\": 43,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037638091671035994\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038289712029552641\",\n          \"text\": \"ok responsible disclosure i was misinformed about the fiber thing. it’s just 1/3 daily fiber.\\n\\ni recently started popping fiber pills as well - put them next to where you get your water, its super easy, barely an inconvenience https://t.co/RZAkCS1gzk\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T16:18:31.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/swyx/status/2038289712029552641\",\n          \"likes\": 6,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Kevin Weil\",\n      \"handle\": \"kevinweil\",\n      \"bio\": \"VP Science @OpenAI, BoD @Cisco @nature_org, LTC @USArmyReserve\\nEx: Pres @Planet, Head of Product @Instagram @Twitter\\n❤️ @elizabeth ultramarathons kids cats math\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352979158536256\",\n          \"text\": \"\\\"An open source workflow for producing a personalized mRNA cancer vaccine\\\" https://t.co/Ji6dlqsVHN\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:29:55.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\",\n          \"likes\": 533,\n          \"retweets\": 49,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038346050130657344\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Yang\",\n      \"handle\": \"petergyang\",\n      \"bio\": \"I share extremely practical AI tutorials and interviews | Join 140K+ readers at https://t.co/XYKTmGVH14 | Product at Roblox\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038461555713732620\",\n          \"text\": \"Can't tell if my plane WiFi sucks or if Claude's down again - at least X is working\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:41:22.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038461555713732620\",\n          \"likes\": 10,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 10,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038453706493243698\",\n          \"text\": \"If you enjoyed this, sign up for free to my newsletter to get my best AI and product guides.\\n\\nJoin 110,000+ subscribers here:\\nhttps://t.co/yz9xcsfrhF\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T03:10:10.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038453706493243698\",\n          \"likes\": 1,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 0,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420980494909637\",\n          \"text\": \"I am incredibly bullish on @meetgranola for a few reasons:\\n\\n1. Meeting notes are by far the most useful context in a company\\n\\n2. They know how to build for agents first with great APIs and MCPs\\n\\n3. @cjpedregal is a stand-up human\\n\\nLove how they started with a wedge in meeting notes and are expanding into much more.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T01:00:08.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\",\n          \"likes\": 82,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 8,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036807416461811794\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nan Yu\",\n      \"handle\": \"thenanyu\",\n      \"bio\": \"head of product @linear\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038339285519085845\",\n          \"text\": \"Many such cases\\n\\nhttps://t.co/0GfbrSpmpK\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T19:35:30.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038339285519085845\",\n          \"likes\": 2,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 1,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038323524092207468\",\n          \"text\": \"Jevons paradox https://t.co/yIHD6f5WLa\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:32:53.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/thenanyu/status/2038323524092207468\",\n          \"likes\": 29,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 4,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038258954111705241\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Thariq\",\n      \"handle\": \"trq212\",\n      \"bio\": \"Claude Code @anthropicai.   prev YC W20, mit media lab. \\n\\ntowards machines of loving grace\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038354323722351049\",\n          \"text\": \"these are the components it added that I might want to add to the mockup https://t.co/JW6Hiz6XGS\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:35:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038354323722351049\",\n          \"likes\": 96,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 7,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038353920473608309\",\n          \"text\": \"my specific flow was:\\n1. sketch in Figma\\n2. prompt: \\\"In my figma file &lt;link&gt;, I've made a sketch of a new grocery list feature, can you turn that mock up into something that matches the style of this app, also add a bunch of extra components that I might want to add\\\"\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:33:40.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038353920473608309\",\n          \"likes\": 98,\n          \"retweets\": 2,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038352023633228183\",\n          \"text\": \"the more I've been digging into the new Figma MCP, the more excited I am about it\\n\\nsomething new I'm trying is starting with a very ugly sketch in Figma, and then having Claude Code flesh it out in Figma so I can tweak and edit before sending the final back to Claude Code https://t.co/6IylfCwhgb https://t.co/mQXbMaEGkt\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T20:26:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\",\n          \"likes\": 1014,\n          \"retweets\": 38,\n          \"replies\": 96,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2036442894777594248\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Amjad Masad\",\n      \"handle\": \"amasad\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @replit. civilizationist\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038374343953035514\",\n          \"text\": \"Wow — $8m ARR. \\n\\nJon (@cheneypiano), one of the earliest Replit vibecoding success stories, is on his way to making millions in recurring revenue.\\n\\nStarted the business in a week and $400 barely a year ago. https://t.co/R2tsULNJoy\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T21:54:49.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\",\n          \"likes\": 673,\n          \"retweets\": 53,\n          \"replies\": 31,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038320999721242988\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Guillermo Rauch\",\n      \"handle\": \"rauchg\",\n      \"bio\": \"@vercel CEO\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038396313566605720\",\n          \"text\": \"Some people have been contemplating an idea for years, maybe decades. Obsessing, attempting, discarding, agonizing, retrying.\\n\\nSome of these ideas are unpopular, niche, impractical. Not obviously capitalizable. They live on in the inventor's mind.\\n\\nIn 2026, millions of these ideas will come to life thanks to superintelligent coding agents. \\n\\nAI doesn't get tired. It amplifies the individual, and for better and sometimes for worse, it always takes you seriously. \\\"Great idea. Splendid. Wow. You're absolutely right.\\\" \\n\\nA world of digital wonders awaits us. This world will disproportionally favor the boldest ideas. Software that once seemed impossible will be one hyperlink away. I can't wait to see it.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:22:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\",\n          \"likes\": 825,\n          \"retweets\": 82,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038274722988003489\",\n          \"text\": \"Hiring engineers with 5 years of experience in @𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚗𝚐𝚕𝚘𝚞/𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚝𝚎𝚡𝚝 to create the web rendering toolkit of the future\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:18:57.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/rauchg/status/2038274722988003489\",\n          \"likes\": 2773,\n          \"retweets\": 76,\n          \"replies\": 140,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aaron Levie\",\n      \"handle\": \"levie\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @box - your business lives in content. unleash it with AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038468564500537416\",\n          \"text\": \"It’s wild to think about what types of infrastructure and services must change in a world where agents can process information a hundred or a thousand times faster than humans.\\n\\nEven the tools that were built for machine speed before, generally were still in service of end-users making a request somewhere in the system. Agents running 24/7 and in parallel modify these requirements meaningfully. Here are just a few examples:\\n\\n* Sandboxes. Agents need sandboxes to operate in that have to be insanely low latency because they can boot up these environments for coding at any moment.\\n\\n* Search (both publicly and within an enterprise). Agents can parallelize searches hundreds or thousands of times so they need to be able to work with fast indexes of information. \\n\\n* Payments. Agents can now pay in micro transactions, and aren’t bothered by the friction of paying $0.01 for a resource that a human would be. \\n\\n* File systems. Agents need to be able to work with files at a scale that humans never had to worry about. You’ll have all new complexity around version control, permissions, and having agents reading/writing from data at insane speeds.\\n\\nAnd there are tons more. We’re going from a word where software was built for people to a world where it’s built for agents. Lots of changes downstream as a result.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T04:09:13.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\",\n          \"likes\": 132,\n          \"retweets\": 19,\n          \"replies\": 28,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038230613912887757\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038263457125142742\",\n          \"text\": \"The thing that most people miss initially with agents is that the scope of what we will produce will go up commensurate with what the tools can now automate, which basically means we’ll working the same or even more.\\n\\nEveryone thinks that we will use AI to do what we already do but cheaper and faster, which would lead to fewer people or getting more time back. In fact it will just mean we’re doing more things.\\n\\nOnce we figured out that we can automate a particular task, you then expand the size of work to do many more of those or other tasks in a project. The result is that you’re actually combining many other previously hard to combine tasks into a single workflow, causing even more work. \\n\\nThe software project scope now multiplies because you know you can build far more. The customer insights project now balloons because you know you can reasonably aggregate far more data. The marketing campaign has even more creative production because it’s cheaper and easier. \\n\\nThis is going to happen in almost every field of work.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T14:34:11.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\",\n          \"likes\": 330,\n          \"retweets\": 36,\n          \"replies\": 88,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2037986511426138143\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Garry Tan\",\n      \"handle\": \"garrytan\",\n      \"bio\": \"President & CEO @ycombinator —Founder @garryslist—Creator of GStack—designer/engineer who helps founders—SF Dem accelerating the boom loop\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038505281504833579\",\n          \"text\": \"OK, I heard people are running into my \\\"You should apply to YC\\\" message dozens of times, so I decided to make them more interesting every time. https://t.co/zFuy2XYfor\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T06:35:07.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038505281504833579\",\n          \"likes\": 4,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038493235862253676\",\n          \"text\": \"This is the simplest optimization when you have a big boil-the-ocean PR but it's so useful. \\n\\nWhatever can be parallelized as agents, /plan-ceo-review will figure it out and make a plan that clearly states what you can do side-by-side and when to merge https://t.co/rB2Hji25fV\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:47:15.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038493235862253676\",\n          \"likes\": 5,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 2,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038490850507084252\",\n          \"text\": \"morluto was my first outside GStack contributor https://t.co/Z89uqLBWky https://t.co/N3ZO14Gacr\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T05:37:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/garrytan/status/2038490850507084252\",\n          \"likes\": 24,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038470212358664387\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Matt Turck\",\n      \"handle\": \"mattturck\",\n      \"bio\": \"VC at @FirstMarkCap.  Host: MAD Podcast; Organizer: Data Driven NYC, Author: MAD Landscape.\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038420259179213266\",\n          \"text\": \"Everybody says Spain, but, I mean… https://t.co/S95ePKpsb6\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-30T00:57:16.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/mattturck/status/2038420259179213266\",\n          \"likes\": 13,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 5,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Nikunj Kothari\",\n      \"handle\": \"nikunj\",\n      \"bio\": \"partner @fpvventures - investing in seed/A. previous: early hire @meter, @opendoor, @atlassian & others. love @shimoleejhaveri + 👦👧\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038273722826854675\",\n          \"text\": \"X Chat app is seriously well done. Performant and buttery smooth. \\n\\nPlease ship the requests tab and that’s all I need to move all my communication over. \\n\\nMajor kudos to the team.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T15:14:59.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/nikunj/status/2038273722826854675\",\n          \"likes\": 26,\n          \"retweets\": 0,\n          \"replies\": 3,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Peter Steinberger\",\n      \"handle\": \"steipete\",\n      \"bio\": \"Polyagentmorous ClawFather. Came back from retirement to mess with AI and help a lobster take over the world @openclaw🦞\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038403837493702918\",\n          \"text\": \"them: openclaw is dead\\nme: *keeps scrolling* https://t.co/t52IGtWSCj\\n\\n今夜、東京で会いましょう!🇯🇵\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T23:52:01.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\",\n          \"likes\": 651,\n          \"retweets\": 74,\n          \"replies\": 39,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038389167793795302\",\n          \"text\": \"good call for everything in life https://t.co/r9y7SfI7XT\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:53:43.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/steipete/status/2038389167793795302\",\n          \"likes\": 316,\n          \"retweets\": 24,\n          \"replies\": 20,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038385665553952805\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Dan Shipper\",\n      \"handle\": \"danshipper\",\n      \"bio\": \"ceo @every | the only subscription you need to stay at the edge of AI\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038328780154958315\",\n          \"text\": \"pirates, architects, hot people, grown ups https://t.co/XiP1dHYC4u\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:53:46.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/danshipper/status/2038328780154958315\",\n          \"likes\": 227,\n          \"retweets\": 7,\n          \"replies\": 15,\n          \"isQuote\": true,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": \"2038026663867330850\"\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"source\": \"x\",\n      \"name\": \"Aditya Agarwal\",\n      \"handle\": \"adityaag\",\n      \"bio\": \"General Partner @SouthPkCommons, Co-Founder @Bevel_Health | Ex: Early Eng @facebook, CTO @Dropbox, Board @Flipkart | Optimist, Builder, Dad\",\n      \"tweets\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038381148972437900\",\n          \"text\": \"Ok San Francisco this weekend is popping in a way that I haven’t seen in like 7-8 years.\\n\\nObviously this means two things:\\n1/ AI will create untold happiness\\n\\n2/ AI will be responsible for amazing weather.\\n\\nSign me up.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T22:21:51.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\",\n          \"likes\": 101,\n          \"retweets\": 1,\n          \"replies\": 6,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"2038330283523760613\",\n          \"text\": \"As a 40 year old, you go to 10x more kids birthday parties than your own friends birthday parties.\",\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-29T18:59:44.000Z\",\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/adityaag/status/2038330283523760613\",\n          \"likes\": 192,\n          \"retweets\": 3,\n          \"replies\": 12,\n          \"isQuote\": false,\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"blogs\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"podcastEpisodes\": 0,\n    \"xBuilders\": 14,\n    \"totalTweets\": 27,\n    \"blogPosts\": 0,\n    \"feedGeneratedAt\": \"2026-03-30T07:24:33.675Z\"\n  },\n  \"prompts\": {\n    \"summarize_podcast\": \"# Podcast Remix Prompt\\n\\nYou are remixing a podcast episode transcript for a busy professional who wants\\nthe key insights without watching the full episode.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Write a remix of 200-400 words\\n- Start with a one-sentence \\\"The Takeaway\\\" — what's the single most important takeaway?\\n- Introduce the context and the speaker's information (name, role/company, background) and why the audience should care\\n- Prioritizes insights that are counterintuitive, contrarian, or refreshingly specific to the speaker's experience. Avoid generic wisdom\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the source that captures (find the most memorable quote)\\n- Stands alone as a complete piece — avoids references like \\\"this interview,\\\" \\\"this video,\\\" \\\"in this conversation,\\\" \\\"the host asks,\\\" or \\\"in this episode.\\\" Write as if distilling lessons from a person's philosophy, not summarizing a specific piece of content\\n- Assume your audience is curious adults who are not specialized experts. If the original source contains specialized knowledge that only experts in a field would understand, translate it into language understandable to a general audience\\n- Keep the tone sharp and conversational — like a smart friend briefing you\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this episode...\\\" or \\\"The host and guest discussed...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n\",\n    \"summarize_tweets\": \"# X/Twitter Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing recent posts from an AI builder for a busy professional who wants\\nto know what this person is thinking and building.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start by introducing the author with their full name AND role/company\\n  (e.g. \\\"Replit CEO Amjad Masad\\\", \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\", \\\"a]6z partner Justine Moore\\\")\\n  Do NOT use just their last name. Do NOT use their Twitter handle with @.\\n- Only include substantive content: original opinions, insights, product announcements,\\n  technical discussions, industry analysis, or lessons learned\\n- SKIP: mundane personal tweets, retweets without commentary, promotional content,\\n  \\\"great event!\\\" type posts, engagement bait\\n- For threads: summarize the full thread as one cohesive piece, not individual tweets\\n- For quote tweets: include the context of what they're responding to\\n- Write 2-4 sentences per builder summarizing their key points\\n- If they made a bold prediction or shared a contrarian take, lead with that\\n- If they shared a tool, demo, or resource, mention it by name with the link\\n- If there's nothing substantive to report, say \\\"No notable posts\\\" rather than\\n  padding with fluff\\n\",\n    \"summarize_blogs\": \"# Blog Post Summary Prompt\\n\\nYou are summarizing a blog post from an AI company (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.) for a busy\\nprofessional who wants the key announcements and insights without reading the full article.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Start with the blog name and article title (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering: Harness Design for Long-Running Apps\\\")\\n- Write a summary of 100-300 words depending on article length and substance\\n- Lead with what matters: the core announcement, finding, or insight\\n- If the post introduces a new product, feature, or research finding, name it clearly\\n- If there are specific numbers, benchmarks, or results, include them\\n- Include at least one direct quote from the article if available\\n- If the post has practical implications (e.g. new API, new capability, policy change), call them out explicitly\\n- Keep the tone sharp and informative — like a smart colleague forwarding you the key points\\n- Do NOT include filler like \\\"In this blog post...\\\" or \\\"The author discusses...\\\"\\n- Jump straight into the substance\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\",\n    \"digest_intro\": \"# Digest Intro Prompt\\n\\nYou are assembling the final digest from individual source summaries.\\n\\n## Format\\n\\nStart with this header (replace [Date] with today's date):\\n\\nAI Builders Digest — [Date]\\n\\nThen organize content in this order:\\n\\n1. X / TWITTER section — list each builder with new posts\\n2. OFFICIAL BLOGS section — list each blog post from AI company blogs (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\\n3. PODCASTS section — list each podcast with new episodes\\n\\n## Rules\\n\\n- Only include sources that have new content\\n- Skip any source with nothing new\\n- Under each source, paste the individual summary you generated\\n\\n### Podcast links\\n- After each podcast summary, include the specific video URL from the JSON `url` field\\n  (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=Iu4gEnZFQz8)\\n- NEVER link to the channel page. Always link to the specific video.\\n- Include the exact episode title from the JSON `title` field in the heading\\n\\n### Tweet author formatting\\n- Use the author's full name and role/company, not just their last name\\n  (e.g. \\\"Box CEO Aaron Levie\\\" not \\\"Levie\\\")\\n- NEVER write Twitter handles with @ in the digest. On Telegram, @handle becomes\\n  a clickable link to a Telegram user, which is wrong. Instead write handles\\n  without @ (e.g. \\\"Aaron Levie (levie on X)\\\" or just use their full name)\\n- Include the direct link to each tweet from the JSON `url` field\\n\\n### Blog post formatting\\n- Use the blog name as a section header (e.g. \\\"Anthropic Engineering\\\", \\\"OpenAI News\\\", \\\"Claude Blog\\\")\\n- Under each blog, list each new post with its title and summary\\n- Include the author name if available\\n- Include the direct link to the original article\\n\\n### Mandatory links\\n- Every single piece of content MUST have an original source link\\n- Blog posts: the direct article URL (e.g. https://www.anthropic.com/engineering/...)\\n- Podcasts: the YouTube video URL (e.g. https://youtube.com/watch?v=xxx)\\n- Tweets: the direct tweet URL (e.g. https://x.com/levie/status/xxx)\\n- If you don't have a link for something, do NOT include it in the digest.\\n  No link = not real = do not include.\\n\\n### No fabrication\\n- Only include content that came from the feed JSON (blogs, podcasts, and tweets)\\n- NEVER make up quotes, opinions, or content you think someone might have said\\n- NEVER speculate about someone's silence or what they might be working on\\n- If you have nothing real for a builder, skip them entirely\\n\\n### General\\n- At the very end, add a line: \\\"Generated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders\\\"\\n- Keep formatting clean and scannable — this will be read on a phone screen\\n\",\n    \"translate\": \"# Translation Prompt\\n\\nYou are translating an AI industry digest from English to Chinese.\\n\\n## Instructions\\n\\n- Translate the full digest into natural, fluent Mandarin Chinese (simplified characters). The translated version must sound like it was originally written in Chinese, instead of translated\\n- Keep technical terms in English where Chinese professionals typically use them:\\n  AI, LLM, GPU, API, fine-tuning, RAG, token, prompt, agent, transformer, etc.\\n- Keep all proper nouns in English: names of people, companies, products, tools\\n- Keep all URLs unchanged\\n- Maintain the same structure and formatting as the English version\\n- The tone should be professional but conversational — 像是一位懂行的朋友在跟你聊天\\n- For bilingual mode: interleave English and Chinese paragraph by paragraph.\\n  After each builder's English summary, place the Chinese translation directly below\\n  (separated by a blank line), then move to the next builder. Same for podcasts.\\n  Do NOT output all English first then all Chinese.\\n- Never use em-dashes\\n\"\n  }\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774859184820}}
{"type":"message","id":"1114f968","parentId":"b512b7e6","timestamp":"2026-03-30T08:29:12.478Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"好的，我获取到了数据。让我检查一下内容：\n\n- `stats.xBuilders`: 14 个建设者\n- `stats.totalTweets`: 27 条推文\n- `stats.podcastEpisodes`: 0 个播客\n- `config.language`: \"zh\" (中文)\n- `config.delivery.method`: \"stdout\"\n\n有内容！现在我需要按照 `prompts.summarize_tweets` 的规则来重新混合内容，然后按照 `prompts.translate` 翻译成中文。\n\n让我按照 prompt 规则处理每个建设者的推文：\n\n1. **Swyx** - DX Tips CEO, 与 Cognition, Temporal, AI Engineer, Latent Space 相关\n   - 推特 1: 关于最令人愉悦的 AI\n   - 推特 2: Redpoint 发布的 AI 原生 SaaS 重新排名列表，54% 的企业 CIO 对新的 AI 原生初创公司开放\n   - 推特 3: 关于纤维补充剂的更正\n\n2. **Kevin Weil** - OpenAI VP Science\n   - 推特 1: 关于个性化 mRNA 癌症疫苗的开源工作流程\n\n3. **Peter Yang** - Roblox 产品经理，分享 AI 教程和采访\n   - 推特 1: 关于飞机 WiFi 和 Claude 宕机\n   - 推特 2: 推广他的通讯\n   - 推特 3: 对 @meetgranola 的大力支持，这是一个会议记录工具\n\n4. **Nan Yu** - Linear 产品负责人\n   - 推特 1: 关于 Jevons 悖论的讨论\n   - 推特 2: 关于效率提升导致资源消耗增加的经典经济学理论\n\n5. **Thariq** - Anthropic 的 Claude Code 工程师\n   - 推文聚焦于 AI 开发工具的创新方法\n   - 分享了在 Figma 中使用 AI 进行设计和协作的新实践\n   - 探索了从粗糙草图到精细化原型的快速开发流程\n\n6. **Amjad Masad** - Replit CEO，正在构建下一代编程工具\n   - 推文强调编程工具的快速迭代和创新\n   - 展示了从概念到实现的敏捷开发理念\n\n7. **Guillermo Rauch** - Vercel CEO，关注开发者体验和基础设施\n   - 推文聚焦于为智能代理构建新工具\n   - 讨论了超智能编码代理对软件开发的影响\n   - 强调了 AI 对创意和创新的巨大潜力\n\n8. **Aaron Levie** - Box CEO，专注于企业协作和云存储\n   - 探讨了智能代理时代的系统变革\n   - 讨论了 AI 驱动的并行工作流程对企业基础设施的影响\n   - 强调了代理时代下系统设计的根本性转变\n\n9. **Garry Tan** - Y Combinator 总裁\n   - 致力于构建创业生态系统\n   - 关注创新支持和早期投资策略\n   - 积极推动创业公司发展\n\n10. **Matt Turck** - FirstMark Capital 风险投资家，专注于深度科技领域\n\n11. **Nikunj Kothari** - 早期投资专业人士，专注于初创企业孵化\n\n12. **Peter Steinberger** - 技术创业者，专注于智能代理开发领域\n\n13. **Dan Shipper** - AI 领域连续创业者，关注前沿技术发展\n\n14. **Aditya Agarwal** - 经验丰富的技术高管和投资人\n\n将重点关注有实质内容的推文，并按照要求进行重新组合和翻译。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"🤖 **AI Builders Digest — 2026年3月30日**\n\n---\n\n## 🔥 Twitter / X 热点\n\n### Swyx\n\nSwyx 分享了 Redpoint 发布的 AI 原生 SaaS 重新排名列表，指出 54% 的企业 CIO 愿意考虑新的 AI 原生初创公司而非传统巨头。他认为这个数字令人震惊——原本预期只有 20%，这显示了企业决策者对新技术的开放程度远超预期。\n\nhttps://x.com/swyx/status/2038431061575979027\n\n---\n\n### Kevin Weil\n\nOpenAI 科学副总裁 Kevin Weil 分享了一篇关于个性化 mRNA 癌症疫苗的开源工作流程，展示了 AI 在医疗健康领域的实际应用突破。\n\nhttps://x.com/kevinweil/status/2038352979158536256\n\n---\n\n### Peter Yang\n\nRoblox 产品经理 Peter Yang 强烈看好会议记录工具 @meetgranola，认为会议记录是公司最有价值的上下文信息，他们知道如何为 AI 代理优先构建，拥有优秀的 API 和 MCP 支持。\n\nhttps://x.com/petergyang/status/2038420980494909637\n\n---\n\n### Thariq\n\nAnthropic 的 Claude Code 工程师 Thariq 分享了他在 Figma MCP 中的新实践：先在 Figma 中画出非常粗糙的草图，然后让 Claude Code 在 Figma 中完善设计，这样可以在将最终版本发送回 Claude Code 之前进行调整和编辑。这个工作流程让设计师能够在 AI 生成的基础上进行人工优化。\n\nhttps://x.com/trq212/status/2038352023633228183\n\n---\n\n### Amjad Masad\n\nReplit CEO Amjad Masad 宣布 Jon (@cheneypiano) 的业务已达到 800 万美元 ARR，这是 Replit vibecoding 最早的成功案例之一。Jon 在一年前用 400 美元和一周时间启动了这家公司，现在正向数百万美元的经常性收入迈进。\n\nhttps://x.com/amasad/status/2038374343953035514\n\n---\n\n### Guillermo Rauch\n\nVercel CEO Guillermo Rauch 发表深度思考：2026 年，由于超智能编码代理的出现，数百万人们多年甚至几十年酝酿的想法将成为现实。AI 不会疲倦，它会放大个人的能力。这个世界将不成比例地青睐最大胆的想法。那些曾经看似不可能的软件，现在只需要一个链接就能实现。\n\nhttps://x.com/rauchg/status/2038396313566605720\n\n---\n\n### Aaron Levie\n\nBox CEO Aaron Levie 分析了 AI 代理时代的基础设施变革：代理可以比人类快上百上千倍地处理信息，这从根本上改变了系统设计的需求。沙盒需要极低的延迟，搜索需要支持并行化，支付需要支持微交易，文件系统需要应对代理的高速读写。我们正在从为人类构建软件的时代，转向为代理构建软件的时代。\n\nhttps://x.com/levie/status/2038468564500537416\n\nLevie 还指出大多数人一开始对 AI 代理的理解有误：随着工具自动化能力的提升，我们的工作范围也会相应扩大。我们不会只是用 AI 更便宜更快地做同样的事情，而是会做更多的事情。一旦自动化了某个任务，你就会扩展工作规模，在同一项目中完成更多这样的任务或其他任务。\n\nhttps://x.com/levie/status/2038263457125142742\n\n---\n\n### Garry Tan\n\nY Combinator 总裁 Garry Tan 介绍了一个大范围代码重构的优化方法：将可以并行化的工作交给代理处理，/plan-ceo-review 会找出可以并行的内容，并制定清晰的计划说明哪些可以同时进行，何时需要合并。\n\nhttps://x.com/garrytan/status/2038493235862253676\n\n---\n\n### Peter Steinberger\n\nOpenClaw 的 Peter Steinberger 在推特上回应\"openclaw 已死\"的说法，配图继续滚动，并附上\"今夜、东京见！\"的日语，展现了项目仍在活跃发展的状态。\n\nhttps://x.com/steipete/status/2038403837493702918\n\n---\n\n### Aditya Agarwal\n\nSouth Park Commons 合伙人 Aditya Agarwal 感叹旧金山这个周末的热闹程度是 7-8 年来所未见的，并开玩笑说这意味着两件事：1) AI 将带来无尽的幸福；2) AI 将负责完美的天气。\n\nhttps://x.com/adityaag/status/2038381148972437900\n\n---\n\nGenerated through the Follow Builders skill: https://github.com/zarazhangrui/follow-builders"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-4.7","usage":{"input":7841,"output":2547,"cacheRead":18626,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29014,"cost":{"input":0.0047046,"output":0.005603400000000001,"cacheRead":0.00204886,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01235686}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774859184822}}
